House: Republican.
Senate: Republican.
White House: Republican.

Republicans are once again dragging our nation toward a government shutdown. Threatening paychecks for federal workers, delaying vital services for families, and destabilizing our economy. Working people will pay the price for their chaos.

Today on @democracynow I spoke about my bill, the No Masks for ICE Act, which would prohibit ICE agents from wearing masks while carrying out arrests and detentions. 

Federal agents should never hide their identity from the public. 

Transparency and accountability are fundamental to protecting civil rights.

Homan built his career smearing immigrants as criminals. Now it looks like he was the crook all along.

The Trump administration is filled with corruption and graft from top to bottom. Homan should be fired and prosecuted. https://t.co/7ETwXB44Li

Eight years ago, María devastated Puerto Rico taking thousands of lives and exposing deep injustices in our recovery.

We remember every loss, every family forced to leave, and every community still rebuilding.

To honor their memory, we keep fighting for equity, dignity, and resilience.
https://t.co/ZFUt113TMr

As storms grow stronger, our communities need stronger protections. 

Yesterday I introduced 5 bills to strengthen disaster response, make flood insurance affordable, and stop price gouging during emergencies. 

Families in NY & PR deserve fairness and support when disaster strikes.

This is cancel culture brought to you by the federal government. 

All part of the Trump admin's ongoing efforts to turn the free press into right-wing state media. 

This is an assault on free speech. If you claim to care about the First Amendment, you must call it out.

Last week, SCOTUS ruled Latinos can be treated as second class citizens, giving ICE a blank check to racially profile our communities.

The Roberts Court is building a shameful legacy of stripping fundamental rights. We will keep fighting for dignity and equality under the law. https://t.co/ILlfw0Pqyx

TODAY: Flood Solutions Fair in Sunnyside! 🌧️

Learn practical steps to protect your home & community.

-Sunnyside Community Services
-1–4 PM | Free & open to all

https://t.co/YOzyVXKPNQ

Bolsonaro tried to overthrow democracy.

Brazil’s courts upheld the law and issued a rebuke to authoritarianism.

Democratic nations should stand firm against attempts to subvert free elections and the US should respect this decision.

At this week’s @NRDems hearing, I voiced my concerns around permitting reform. 

While I support accelerating renewable energy development, we cannot allow a pro–fossil fuel, anti–clean energy administration that disregards the climate crisis to weaken NEPA. 

These protections must be strengthened, not rolled back.

Today marks 24 years since nearly 3,000 lives were stolen on one of the darkest days in our nation’s and New York’s history on 9/11.

We honor the courage of first responders, survivors, and all who carried us through. We will never forget their sacrifice.

In the face of this unimaginable tragedy, New Yorkers came together and rebuilt our city. That spirit must guide us still today.

The devastation in Gaza is unbearable. Entire families gone, neighborhoods erased, too often caused by bombs stamped Made in the USA.

That’s why I support @repdeliaramirez Block the Bombs Act. No more blank checks for war and US weapons fueling genocide. We must demand peace. https://t.co/oRkfnRwuXg

I am shocked and appalled by the shooting of Charlie Kirk at Utah Valley University. Violence—especially political violence—has no place in our society.

My thoughts are with Kirk, his loved ones, and all those present.

Carmelo Anthony — son of Brooklyn, Knicks legend, and proud Boricua — has been inducted into the Basketball Hall of Fame.

Congratulations, Melo!

Amazon fired over 100 unionized delivery drivers in Queens as part of their union-busting campaign.

It's immoral when a trillion-dollar corporation tries to crush organizing efforts in our communities.

Workers’ rights are non-negotiable. Solidarity with @AmazonTeamsters.

The way we look, the language we speak, the accent we carry should never be grounds for ICE to detain us.

Today's SCOTUS ruling greenlights racial profiling, undermines due process, and tells Latinos our dignity is optional. This court is trampling the Constitution.
This is the man that says he's not in the files. https://t.co/0IhonmIB12

RFK Jr.’s lies in the Senate were dangerous. Undermining science and dismantling public health protections puts millions at risk.
 
He has no business in government. He must resign or be removed immediately.

🚨THIS SATURDAY🚨

Join my office for a Flood Solutions Fair in Western Queens! 

RSVP NOW: https://t.co/0aGsA3khiS

When: September 13, 1PM – 4:00PM
Where: Sunnyside Community Services 43-31 39th Street Queens, NY

Ask experts in your community how you can take action to protect against flooding. Plumbers, landscapers, masons, basement waterproofers, insurance representatives, elected officials, citizen advocates, and NGOs will be in attendance.

Another life stolen by our jail system's brutality.

Jimmy Avila died at Rikers just as Musa Cetin and Christopher Nieves lost their lives in NYPD custody.

City leadership has failed. Accountability cannot wait. We need transparency, justice, and end to systemic negligence now.

No one should face discrimination for presenting a valid Puerto Rico Real ID. 

What happened to Mr. Rivera at Walmart in Ohio is unacceptable. 

I’m calling on Walmart’s CEO to investigate and ensure this never happens again. https://t.co/IPS2qYRKXJ

Sending in troops to police our neighborhoods is an assault on our democracy.
 
Communities deserve safety and dignity, not intimidation from a wannabe dictator. Our cities are not battlegrounds. https://t.co/MIswcAG5oy

America is built on democracy, not military rule. Trump is using DC as a testing ground for his authoritarianism. 

This threatens our freedoms, fuels fear & undermines all we stand for.

Our communities will not be terrorized by a wannabe dictator. Donald Trump, stay the hell away from our cities.

During his more than 30 years in Congress, my dear friend @RepJerryNadler has never stopped fighting for New Yorkers.

From impeaching Trump, to defending reproductive rights, to protecting civil liberties after 9/11, Jerry always had the courage to do what’s right.

New York City and our nation are better because of him. His impact on Congress won’t soon be forgotten

Millions of Americans, especially communities of color, are still living with the consequences of outdated marijuana laws.

The MORE Act is about justice, second chances, and opportunity. Proud to join @RepJerryNadler and my colleagues in this fight.

The start of the school year should be a time of celebration. Instead, families in Minneapolis are facing the unimaginable. My heart is with the victims, their classmates, & their families.

Gun violence is stealing our kids’ futures. We can't accept this as normal. We must act.

Trump desmanteló la JSF alegando ‘eficiencia’. Ahora vemos la realidad: se gastarán más recursos de los puertorriqueños para negociar con bonistas, luego de que BlackRock se uniera a GoldenTree para pedir más, pese a que antes estaban conformes con el Plan de Ajuste.

El resultado de la movida de Trump: BlackRock y GoldenTree más fuertes, exigiendo más a costa del pueblo, lo que resultaría en alzas en la luz de hasta $40 mensuales por residente. Seguiré denunciando estos planes y abogando por un PAD viable en el tiempo. Es lo mínimo que cada puertorriqueño merece.

Israel’s deliberate, horrific strikes on Nasser Hospital killed doctors, journalists, and rescue workers. A hospital should never be a war zone.

The U.S. cannot keep funding these war crimes.

ICE’s arrest of Kilmar Abrego this morning is another brutal reminder that we are living under a government that uses fear, detention, and deportation as weapons. 

This is the machinery of a fascist state tearing families apart. #FreeKilmar

The proposed NESE fracked gas pipeline is a direct threat to New York’s climate goals. At a time when we should be investing in clean energy, this project would lock us into decades of fossil fuel dependence and place environmental justice communities at greatest risk.

I’m calling on @NYSDEC to reject this dangerous pipeline and protect our people, our harbor, and our future.

Mouctar is part of our Brooklyn classrooms and community. He poses no threat to anyone.

Our students are not targets. Free Mouctar Diallo.

For 90 years, Social Security has been a lifeline for millions of Americans, ensuring dignity and stability in retirement, for people with disabilities, and for families who’ve lost a loved one. 

We must honor this legacy by protecting and strengthening it for generations to come.

For months, the Trump admin has blocked me & my colleagues from inspecting 26 Federal Plaza. 

This ruling is more proof they've been hiding abusive, illegal conditions. 

Judge Kaplan’s order is progress, but we won’t stop until the 10th floor ICE detention site is shut down.

Proud to lead the call with my @DemWomenCaucus colleagues urging DHS to act against ICE impersonators attacking women.

Trump’s masked ICE raids make it easier for predators to strike

My No Masks for ICE Act would end these tactics for good.

On Jan 6, as the Capitol was under attack, Trump refused to call in the National Guard. He later pardoned those who beat police and tried to overturn the election.

Now, with DC crime at a 30-year low, he’s sending in the Guard in an authoritarian power grab. We must stand against it, or other cities will be next.

Trump is launching a baseless investigation against @NewYorkStateAG because she dared to hold him accountable. He is weaponizing the DOJ to punish his political opponents, plain and simple.

AG James is a fighter for New Yorkers, and we are proud to stand with her.

Netanyahu’s plan will only bring more suffering. More than 60K Palestinians have already been killed, over 150K injured, & mass starvation is rampant. 

This won't make Israelis or Palestinians safe. The US must stop funding this violence & do everything possible to end the war.

Eddie Palmieri lived an incredible life. A proud Puerto Rican and true pioneer of Latin music, his sound shaped generations and put our culture on the map.

New York, Puerto Rico and the world will miss him. Que descanse en paz.

Last night, I joined neighbors, community leaders, and local precincts across NY-07 for National Night Out.
 
From Brooklyn to Queens, we came together to celebrate community and commit to building safer, stronger neighborhoods for all. https://t.co/m8TOosNegL

Today, @RepEspaillat, @RepDanGoldman, and I were locked out of MDC Brooklyn and denied our legal right to conduct oversight.
 
This facility has a long record of abuse and is now detaining immigrants in secret.

The Trump admin is blocking oversight of their lawless deportation machine. The public deserves answers.

Trump’s Fiscal Board purge isn’t about reform.

It’s a move to stack the Board with people who will keep putting hedge funds first, leaving Puerto Ricans to pay the price.

I’ll keep fighting for a just recovery & the day Puerto Ricans can govern without unelected control. https://t.co/3MK07xwRJ8

Greg Abbott is now ordering the arrest of lawmakers for standing up to Donald Trump's corrupt, gerrymandered map.

Texas Democrats are defending democracy while Republicans resort to authoritarian tactics to cling to power. We've got their back.

I led a letter with Reps. Hernández and McCollum urging the U.S. Air Force to expand SBIR/STTR innovation grants to small businesses and universities in Puerto Rico and other U.S. territories.

It’s time for equity in federal innovation funding. The territories must be included. https://t.co/2nbzJaFtBC

Telling the truth seems to be the only fireable offense in the Trump administration.

Firing the BLS Commissioner won’t cover up the wreckage Trump’s economic agenda is leaving behind. 

It just deepens the public’s mistrust in the economy and the numbers we rely on.

Trump promised not to touch Medicaid. He lied.

Now our hospitals and our communities are bracing for the biggest health care cuts in US history.

I gathered frontline workers and patients at Wyckoff to say: we won’t go down without a fight.
https://t.co/dVoIRrvMht

Today, New Yorkers honored the life of NYPD Det. Didarul Islam, a devoted husband, father, and hero who gave his life to save others. 

He came to this country seeking opportunity and built a life of service protecting New Yorkers. 

My heart is with his family, his fellow officers, and the Bangladeshi-American community during this time of profound grief.

On Medicaid's 60th anniversary, I gathered health care workers, hospital leaders, and patients at Wyckoff in Bushwick to speak out against the GOP’s massive health care cuts.
 
This is the biggest attack on care in our nation’s history and we won't stop fighting. https://t.co/Vo0Srw1fzm

Attention NY-07 students: The Congressional App Challenge is now open!
 
If you're a middle or high school student with a passion for technology and innovation, I invite you to develop and submit your own original app. Your work could be showcased in the U.S. Capitol.
 
Learn more & apply: 👉https://t.co/JpXVwd7STT

First, they gutted Medicaid. Now they’re coming for Social Security, and they’re not even trying to hide it.

We won’t let them rip away a benefit that millions of Americans have worked their whole lives to earn.

Awdah Hathaleen, a teacher, father and activist, was shot & killed by an Israeli settler while standing in his own village. 

The settler had been sanctioned by the US for violent attacks on Palestinians, but Trump lifted those penalties.

His murder is the result of US and Israeli policies that ignore and enable settler violence in the West Bank. He deserves justice.

Telling Dreamers to “self-deport” is nothing short of cruel. These are young people who grew up here, went to school here, and built their lives here.

This is their home, and I will not stop fighting for them.

Heartbroken by the shooting in Midtown that has taken multiple lives, including an off-duty NYPD officer.

My thoughts are with their families, and I’m praying for all the victims who were injured.

Grateful to the NYPD for their quick response in such a terrifying moment.

The US must use all tools to surge aid, secure a permanent ceasefire, & stop this catastrophe.https://t.co/z3g0Cytngi

In Puerto Rico, nonprofits have stepped in where the government hasn’t.
 
But with 84% relying on federal funding, Trump’s cuts to critical grant programs are devastating. These groups are lifelines. Defunding them means defunding survival.

Families in Gaza are starving. Children are dying. People searching for food are being shot.

Israel is blocking aid, and over 100 humanitarian groups are sounding the alarm.

The U.S. must act now to end the blockade and get life-saving aid to civilians. This is an emergency.

Desde su llegada, LUMA ha agravado la crisis energética en Puerto Rico con una gestión marcada por la negligencia.

Doy la bienvenida a Notificación de Disputas a LUMA Energy de parte de @AAPPPuertoRico .

Este debe ser un proceso justo, transparente y enfocado en el bienestar del pueblo.

Estoy lista para colaborar por un Puerto Rico más justo y resiliente.

Since its arrival, LUMA has deepened the energy crisis in Puerto Rico with a management marked by negligence.

I welcome @AAPPPuertoRico Notice of Disputes to LUMA Energy.

This must be a fair, transparent process focused on the welfare of the people.

I am ready to collaborate for a fairer and more resilient Puerto Rico.
Republicans cancelling votes:

Too many families are still living this nightmare. We must keep fighting until they are reunited.

We need transparency now. Release the files.

Today, I reintroduced The Texture Positive Act of 2025 to invest in inclusive training by partnering with women & minority-led experts. It’s time to close the gap. https://t.co/6spIQYllCs

He desperately wants us to look away. So do House Republicans.

We’re not letting this go. Release the files.

Sayfollah "Saif" Musallet was a 20-year-old American visiting family in the West Bank for the summer. He was beaten to death by Israeli settlers.

The U.S. must immediately launch a full, independent investigation and demand accountability for his death.

Mañana: No te pierdas la vista “La Recuperación Fiscal de Puerto Rico bajo PROMESA y el Camino por Delante”

Tune in to hear the truth about the Fiscal Board, the impact on Puerto Ricans, and what lies ahead.

The Supreme Court just cleared the way for Trump to gut the Department of Education.

This is a direct attack on public education and the families who rely on it. 

While billionaires get more tax breaks, our kids get less.
¡Gracias, Amanda Serrano, por poner en alto la bandera de Puerto Rico! Orgullo boricua dentro y fuera del ring. Nueva York y la Isla están contigo. 🇵🇷🥊
Thank you, Amanda Serrano, for raising Puerto Rico’s flag high! Boricua pride in and out of the ring. New York and the Island stand with you. 🇵🇷🥊

Alongside @SenSchumer and @SenGillibrand, I led 19 NY Democrats in demanding the immediate release of these funds. Our kids can’t wait.

Después de décadas de silencio, por fin empieza a salir la verdad a la luz.

Luego de una carta enviada por @RepAOC y por mí, el FBI finalmente ha revelado nuevos detalles sobre el asesinato de Carlos Muñiz Varela.

Seguiré exigiendo verdad y justicia. Puerto Rico merece respuestas. 🇵🇷

After decades of silence, light is breaking through. 

Following a letter from @RepAOC & I, the FBI has finally released additional details on the murder of Carlos Muñiz Varela. 

I will continue to press on for truth and justice. Puerto Rico deserves answers. 🇵🇷✊🏽

⚠️Thunderstorm Alert for NYC⚠️

Stay safe and stay informed. Heavy rain, strong winds, and possible flooding expected. Check on neighbors and avoid travel if possible. https://t.co/WeT2WUTsrn

When EPA workers raise the alarm about cuts that endanger our communities, they deserve protection not punishment.

Putting 139 public servants on leave for speaking out is retaliation, plain and simple.
 
We can’t build climate justice by silencing the very people fighting for it.

Happy Fourth of July! Wishing everyone in NY-7 a joyful and safe day.

Today we celebrate the promise of freedom, and recommit to building a country where liberty and justice truly applies to all.

Today, the GOP, including every NY Republican, voted to make America sicker, hungrier, & poorer — just to give billionaires more tax breaks.
 
I refuse to stay silent while they gut Medicaid, shut down hospitals, & take food off families’ tables. We won’t forget this betrayal. https://t.co/HdqX5xoMjV

The House Republican budget is a direct attack on Puerto Rican students.

They’re slashing Pell Grants, gutting work-study, killing subsidized loans, and pushing low-income borrowers into 30-year debt traps, all while restarting brutal collections.

This is a war on education and working-class students.

I won’t stand by while they try to shut the doors of opportunity on Puerto Rico. 

Kill the bill!

Spent all morning on the House floor with @RepJeffries as Republicans tried to jam through their despicable bill.

He laid out exactly what’s at stake: cuts to health care, cuts to food assistance, & so many Americans who will be hurt just to give billionaires another tax break.

The Trump admin is unlawfully withholding $7B from after-school programs, & I’ve already heard from NYC schools that say the delay will impact their ability to run summer programming for hundreds of students.

This is cruel, chaotic, and illegal. Release the money now.

The Big Ugly Bill is a gift to billionaires and a gut punch to working families.

I stood with my colleagues today to say: we won’t let greed write our laws. https://t.co/9yLVoXF2I0

Republicans are pushing the biggest Medicaid cut in US history.  

Up to 1.5 M New Yorkers could lose their insurance. Constituents with serious health conditions have told me point blank they won’t survive without Medicaid.  

Just 4 House Republicans can stop this madness.

Senate Republicans just voted to starve the poor, strip healthcare from families, and defund education so the rich can get another damn tax break.

They call it the “Big, Beautiful Bill.” There’s nothing beautiful about greed and cruelty.

NO MASKS FOR ICE ACT: I introduced a bill to stop ICE from wearing masks and hiding their identities during enforcement.
 
It’s time for transparency. It’s time for accountability.
 
Call your Representative and ask them to cosponsor H.R. 4004. https://t.co/QNbFkCjGVt

Today, we stood outside the ICE detention facility at 26 Federal Plaza to say loud and clear: NO MASKS FOR ICE.

These tactics are creating chaos and facilitating abuse. 

It’s time to pass my bill and bring basic accountability to immigration enforcement. https://t.co/YNwk3fcWJz

The Supreme Court just opened the door for Trump’s assault on birthright citizenship.

As Justice Sotomayor warned in her dissent, “No right is safe in the new legal regime the Court creates.”

This ruling is an attack on the very foundation of our nation.

¡Un juez federal acaba de frenar el cierre de los centros de Job Corps  incluyendo los de Puerto Rico! 

Lideré el llamado al @USDOL para proteger este programa vital que brinda educación, capacitación y vivienda gratuita a 25,000 jóvenes.

Esta es una gran victoria y la lucha continúa.

A federal judge just halted the shutdown of Job Corps centers, including in Puerto Rico!

I led the charge urging @USDOL to protect this vital program, which offers free education, training & housing to 25K youth.

This is a big win and the fight isn’t over.

The unhinged racism and xenophobia from my Republican colleagues truly knows no bounds.

This is disgraceful behavior from a Member of Congress, but sadly, exactly what we've come to expect from this caucus.

As co-chairs of the Hepatitis Caucus, @RepHankJohnson and I sent a letter to RFK Jr. after he removed trusted vaccine experts and opened the door to dangerous pseudoscience.
 
Rolling back hepatitis vaccine guidelines will cost lives.
 
We won’t stay silent while science is dismantled and public health is threatened.
https://t.co/wKYPCuI5R6

Amber Thurman. Candi Miller. Josseli Barnica. Porsha Ngumezi. Nevaeh Crain.
 
On the anniversary of the Dobbs decision, we say their names because silence is not an option.
 
They should be alive today—but abortion restrictions denied them care and cost them their lives.
 
I will keep fighting to restore reproductive rights and end these cruel, deadly policies.
 
We demand justice.

If Mike Johnson won’t follow through, we will.
 
The plaque honoring the officers who defended the Capitol on January 6 still hasn’t been installed—because Republican leadership refuses to act.
 
So we’ve placed replicas outside our offices as a reminder: their sacrifice won’t be buried by politics.

Trump’s illegal strikes on Iran risk dragging the US into another disastrous endless conflict & endanger countless innocent lives across the region.

The American people don't want this.

Congress must pass the War Powers Resolution & stop Trump’s unconstitutional march to war.

If you're having trouble with a federal agency, my office is here to help. Don’t hesitate to reach out.

The Trump admin jailed Mahmoud Khalil for over 3 months, not because he committed a crime but because he exercised his free speech rights.

I'm relieved he'll finally be reunited with his family.

Juneteenth reminds us that freedom was delayed for far too many.

On this day in 1865, the last enslaved people in Galveston, Texas finally learned they were free. 

Today, we celebrate Black liberation and keep pushing for true justice and equality.

The US cannot be dragged into another endless war in the Middle East.

Congress must assert its constitutional authority and prohibit an unauthorized war with Iran. https://t.co/DZmHEBGhUo

Brad Lander was violently arrested for standing up for immigrant rights and asking ICE to see a warrant.
 
This is yet another authoritarian attack on anyone who dares to hold the Trump administration accountable.
 
He must be released immediately.

Americans do not want war with Iran, and only Congress has the power to declare one.

We must not allow the US to be dragged into another endless conflict.

Proud to join this resolution.

Last week, I pressed Interior Secretary Burgum on delays to vital offshore wind projects.

NYers want clean energy, good union jobs, & real climate action. Not more fossil fuels. https://t.co/pj1Lj9MxyI

There is no place for this in our politics. We all must stand together to reject political violence.
Speaker Johnson, it’s not my fault that you can’t handle the truth about January 6th. https://t.co/1Qx6M87yy0

You don’t get to target @senalexpadilla for speaking the truth & standing up for immigrants.
 
Congressional leadership must defend the rights of every member. We won’t back down.

.@SenAlexPadilla was manhandled and detained for attending a public DHS press conference.

The Trump administration is trying to silence protestors, journalists, and even U.S. Senators.

This is authoritarian behavior. We need a full investigation. I stand with Senator Padilla.

ICE agents hiding their faces and badges spreads fear and eliminates accountability for abuse. These secret police tactics don’t belong in our democracy.

Today, I introduced the No Masks for ICE Act to bring basic transparency and accountability to immigration enforcement. https://t.co/r2yqXxtHcd

I introduced the Police Not ICE Act with @RepThompson
to stop ICE and CBP from masquerading as local police and terrorizing immigrant communities.
